Text:
@people You wrote a whole article about a tongue-in-cheek tweet?

No wonder this world has a problem with the deification of celebrities.

They literally breathe and you're ready to write an essay on it like it's some monumental thing.

@Merman_Melville Did you know that by not helping others he's also hurting them?

Financial inequality/instability is one of the leading causes of depression and anxiety in 1st World Countries.

Elon Musk is one of the reasons I don't want to live in this world anymore. It's just not fair.

@thetimes "Will claims of "illegal" behaviour harm Boris Johnson?"

No, because this world provides loopholes and exemptions for the rich and famous whilst they keep their feet on people's heads to prevent social mobility.

The world loves them and hates anybody who isn't them.

@GemLeighton I used to love writing but when I was 9 a teacher told me "You have no creativity and you're just not very good".

I went on to get a degree in Creative Writing.

Also I think it's a great picture! Well done Edie.

@Telegraph Unless you got a house that can be bought for a few buttons I found down the back of the sofa, these aren't going to be in my price range.

I'm never going to be able to afford to move out and it's one of the reasons I don't want to be around.

I'm not enjoying my one life.

@Mpkzzz1 @GlamourMagUK And it shouldn't be.

Too many people go through life miserable and when asked why they just say "That's just life" and it shouldn't be. It can be changed.

Why should your situation of birth depend on whether you're going to struggle to pay for food and rent or not?

@DanPriceSeattle This is the kind of stuff that makes me wonder if life is worth living.

For most of us we'll spend our lives worried about rent and bills and I'm probably going to end up homeless. It could be solved if these people didn't hoard money and helped others.

I hate this world.

@StreamtheVote "If you have enough followers you can truly do whatever the fuck you want."

That's the truest statement I've heard in a long time.

And it's also really depressing.

@GlamourMagUK Let me do the "I didn't expect this post to blow up so here's something, please support me".

Okay so I haven't written on this for a few months (due to lack of support/mental health issues) but I'd love to get back into it and would love support. ‚ù§Ô∏è

https://t.co/PinaheK03O

@Telegraph A budget of ¬£500,000?!

I'll never see that amount in my lifetime given my future prospects and current job situation.

Oh well, guess I'll just end up homeless.

@EvanEdinger If you have the right support and a face that fits.

As somebody who made over a hundred videos on YouTube with an average of 1 view per video, it's not as "fun" and as "easy" as people make it out.

It made me realise this world doesn't want me around though.

@lloydhardy @pritipatel Is this what she's claiming on expenses? As in this is what the tax-payer pays for?

That's about ¬£130,000.

Just as an FYI, it'll take me close to 22 years to earn that (assuming I had zero outgoings).

@BBCTheOneShow @OwainWynEvans Nothing will change because change is inconvenient.

If anything should have changed it should have seen the demise of celebrity culture and the rise in pay for essential workers.

That didn't happen, all essential workers got were a couple of claps then forgotten about.

@guardiannews ¬£120m.

Just think how many people could be helped with that money and instead they're gonna waste it on what is essentially a big party.

But ¬£120m to the Tories is pocket money.

@thismorning If sitting apart is your biggest worry then realise your privilege.

You still get paid hundreds of thousands of pounds to do very little while others on the frontline get paid pittance. Not to mention those who have lost their jobs during this pandemic.

#ThisMorning

@thesundaytimes This is because this world isn't about what you know, it's about who you know.

People say others can't help you and you've got to help yourself, but these people are living proof that with the right help you CAN do anything.

But yeah, this is sickening nepotism.

@TelGlobalHealth @Harrietmbarber @MentalHealth1M Then how about we actually help people with mental health problems?

Oh, wait, it's because we're too busy funnelling money into celebrity pockets.

And because people only care when celebrities are "struggling" because us below aren't important.

@lia_nici @JamesSunderl @BBCBreakfast @BBCNews @Ofcom @bbcpress Yeah because moving abroad has never been easier with Brexit.

And why should we be proud of the Queen? The Royal Family is just quintessential nepotism.

And a flag is just a fucking flag. Calm down.

@CalumASMR It's sad but true.

Depression and lack of self-worth/esteem has literally taken away everything from me.

It's worse because you're still one of my favourite ASMRtists and I really want to support you.

@nytimes Corruption?! In business focused around celebrities?! Who would've thought it!

Hell, at least yours is just an award they're not nominating you for.

Get back to me when they don't care if you live or die because you're "not important enough" or worth their time.

@outstndnbrandon As a British person who was obsessed with America for years, I could ace it.

Fun fact; because of an episode of Friends I learned how to name all 50 states in alphabetical order (and can do it in under 30 seconds).

Yeah, that's my weird flex.

@rianne088 I agree but my issue is that celebrities wouldn't care if you or I had suicidal thoughts so why are we supposed to care about them?

If celebs had the choice they'd leave you hanging from a cliff if nobody was looking.

Yet they're the ones who get all the support from others.

@WSJ Great, so I just gotta get $175,000 first.

Maybe I'll start looking down the back of the couch.

I'd be over the fucking moon with $175,000.

@Hardly26375072 @MailOnline Because she was short of job options?

What about up-and-coming journalists or those that have worked for years without recognition? What about giving everybody a fair chance in life?

Sod it, let's just bring in another celeb right?

@nazirafzal Unfortunately you are one of a few.

As somebody who has and does still feel suicidal at times, whenever I've spoken about my mental health it's always been met with hostility, ridicule and bullying.

Piers' reaction to Meghan Markle is sadly the norm for most suffering.

This is a great things to do but they won't do it for everybody.

@MindCharity are only doing this because there's celebs involved.

In my experience all #mentalhealth charities will do for regular people is give you signposts and phone numbers to other companies who do nothing. https://t.co/mjrDn3mTsg

@ITV @GMB are supposed to be running a campaign about about good #mentalhealth and so day one they have a presenter accuse somebody of lying about suicidal thoughts and day two they bring on her father who she has a bad relationship with.

Nice going.

#goodmorningbritain

@GMB @susannareid100 @piersmorgan And you're not a psychiatrist or a Doctor, you have no right passing that kind of judgement when you know you're being watched by millions.

ITV have the #BritainGetTalking campaign but you're stopping people talking out of fear of not being believed.

It's very damaging.

@CourtneyCrucio_ @eleshepp Wait till they realise the celebrities couldn't care less about them.

Also, whether you meant to or not, your comment says the world values celebrities more than normal people and that it's okay.

Everybody should be valued. Everybody who is struggling should be supported.

@DanPriceSeattle @rustyrockets I have been saying this for years!

Thank you! Thank you! Thank you!

Those at the top do the bare minimum to appear to be nice people and to completely ignore doing anything else for people because of the "I donated millions! That's more than you've done!" attitude.

Read the room;

The world has billionaires. Millions of millionaires. People who make sure money stays in their hands and not in the hands of those "below them".

We can afford to pay people more than buttons if we stopped paying certain people millions for doing nothing.

@DanPriceSeattle If this doesn't make you sick or angry then you're not a person I want to know.

Nobody does enough to deserve that kind of money.

Not a single person.

@grieve51166 If they're replacing Bradley then they should give a chance to somebody newer.

Schofield already earns 700k from just #ThisMorning. Not to mention the obscene amounts he probably earns from adverts, Dancing On Ice, The Cube, Book Deals etc.

He doesn't need another show.

@damianburns Cameo is just celebrities saying "we're too important to talk to you unless you're paying us" so I don't particularly feel sorry for celebrities.

Anyway, they haven't cared about the numerous things that have affected the lives of people beneath them.

Fuck them.

@DanPriceSeattle Because unfortunately the world doesn't care about us at the bottom.

The world caters to celebrities and millionaires who literally couldn't give a crap if we lived or died.

Most won't even take 30 seconds to change somebody's life because it doesn't benefit them to do so.

@Endlockdowns1 Well that got condescending at the end there, thanks.

And it's an injection that prevents a virus, it's not installing a chip or shit like that. You're making a wild leap to Nazis.

And it's not the same kind of segregation if you actively choose not to get the vaccine.
